		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Robert G. Ingersoll</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">For other persons named Robert Ingersoll, see <a href="/wiki/Robert_Ingersoll" title="Robert Ingersoll">Robert Ingersoll</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Robert_G._Ingersoll_-_Brady-Handy.jpg" class="image" title="Robert G. Ingersoll"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2a/Robert_G._Ingersoll_-_Brady-Handy.jpg/180px-Robert_G._Ingersoll_-_Brady-Handy.jpg" width="180" height="238" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Robert_G._Ingersoll_-_Brady-Handy.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Robert G. Ingersoll</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Colonel <b>Robert Green Ingersoll</b> (August 11, 1833 – July 21, 1899) was a <a href="/wiki/American_Civil_War" title="American Civil War">Civil War</a> veteran, <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> political leader, and <a href="/wiki/Orator" title="Orator">orator</a> during the <a href="/wiki/Golden_Age_of_Freethought" title="Golden Age of Freethought">Golden Age of Freethought</a>, noted for his broad range of culture and his defense of <a href="/wiki/Agnosticism" title="Agnosticism">agnosticism</a>.</p>
